caption: Really good chicken for me the best in my city

Popeyes is my goto for the Chicken Sandwich wars. I also like their fries. I was in this area and visited this store for the first time in a long time. There is no Drive-Thru so walk-in counter service is the only option as of this writing. There are two customers ahead of me. The staff's demeanor is flat and robotic, going thru the motions on a day at work. I ordered the Chicken Sandwich Combo w/ Fries.  Food came out quickly. I asked for two sauces but was told I could have only one with a sandwich combo. The sandwich was hot, crispy and familiar. The taste and temp of the fries was fine but the quantity was minimal compared to more generous portions at other Popeyes I've been to.  This store must be working on their food costs by portion control and limiting post-sale condiments. It was roughly 2p so I can't judge the activity of the store based on this one experience. I'd like like to give them another chance but won't go in with high expectations.

Each container was literally barely half way full when we arrived at home and opened them.  We should have checked prior to leaving but they have never been that empty before. It was literally a few spoonfuls and not even enough for 2 people.  The mac & cheese was almost entirely water.  It pretty much washed the cheese off the mac. The chicken was overcooked so much that it looked as if it had shrunken half it's size. The slaw was okay but just under halfway filled up.  They weren't busy when we ordered otherwise it would be a bit more understandable.  We won't be returning for quite sometime.
